# GitHub Pages Deployment

This project is deployed to GitHub Pages using the **legacy** (branch-based) mode.
The project files are committed to the `docs/` directory on `main`, and GitHub serves it directly.

**Live URL**: https://bookish-memory-p3er739.pages.github.io/

## How It Works

source files → copy to docs/ → push to main → GitHub Pages serves docs/

- Source `.html`, `.js`, `.css` files are in the project root
- `docs/` is committed (GitHub Pages source)
- `.nojekyll` in `docs/` disables Jekyll processing

## Agent Instructions

A **pre-commit hook** automatically copies updated files to `docs/` whenever HTML/JS/CSS files are staged.
Do NOT manually copy files to `docs/` — the hook handles it during `git commit`.

### Shell permissions

Use standard git commands. The pre-commit hook will automatically sync changes to `docs/`.

### If the hook is missing

Git hooks are not tracked by git and can be lost after a re-clone. If `git commit`
does not produce "Updating docs/ for GitHub Pages..." output, reinstall the hook:

```bash
cat > .git/hooks/pre-commit << 'HOOK'
#!/bin/sh
STAGED=$(git diff --cached --name-only --diff-filter=d | grep -E '\.(html|js|css)$' | grep -v '^docs/')
if [ -z "$STAGED" ]; then exit 0; fi
echo "Updating docs/ for GitHub Pages..."
mkdir -p docs
cp *.html *.js *.css docs/ 2>/dev/null
touch docs/.nojekyll
git add docs/
echo "docs/ updated."
HOOK
chmod +x .git/hooks/pre-commit
```

